1
00:00:04,505 --> 00:00:05,506
[Growls]

2
00:00:05,589 --> 00:00:06,715
[Dolphins chatter]

3
00:00:10,302 --> 00:00:11,428
[Screeches]

4
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:14,306
J Adventure time J

5
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:15,641
J Come on, grab your friends &

6
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:18,477
> We'll go
to very distant lands 7

7
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,771
J With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong J

8
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:22,397
J And possibly BMO 7

9
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:24,274
J It's adventure time 7

10
00:00:33,951 --> 00:00:37,079
KARA: We're closing in on
Minerva's brainwave signature.

11
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:41,333
We should touch down
in just a few minutes.

12
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:42,167
Whoa.

13
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:44,711
So, that's what my mom's
thoughts look like.

14
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,464
They look good.
I think.

15
00:00:47,589 --> 00:00:49,341
Hold on.

16
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:51,843
Whoa.

17
00:00:51,927 --> 00:00:53,470
That's her?

18
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:56,098
KARA: Mm-hmm.
Dr. Minerva.

19
00:01:01,979 --> 00:01:03,355
She looks nice.

20
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:04,523
[Beeping]

21
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:05,899
We're here, Finn.

22
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:08,819
Buckle up.
I'm gonna take us down.

23
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,450
FINN:
Humans.

24
00:01:15,534 --> 00:01:17,327
There's so many.

25
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:19,580
Are they friendly, Kara?
The people here?

26
00:01:19,663 --> 00:01:23,333
[Chuckles] Don't worry.
You're gonna fit right in.

27
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:53,238
KARA:
Finn? Finn?

28
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:54,573
Hey, listen.

29
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:56,241
I remember enough
about my old life

30
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:58,619
to know that there were
some dangerous people here.

31
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:00,329
So let's stick together, okay?

32
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:02,331
And let's all try
to keep a low profile.

33
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:05,000
Minerva! Minerva!

34
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,501
Hey, you, where's Minerva?

35
00:02:06,585 --> 00:02:08,086
Wha! Geez.

36
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:10,297
You scared me
with that costume, citizen.

37
00:02:10,297 --> 00:02:12,924
Don't change the subject.
Now, where's Minerva?

38
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:14,926
And does she have any chips
or crackers or anything?

39
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:16,928
I'm getting real tired
of picking batteries

40
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,764
out of these BMO cakes.

41
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:21,266
Where's Minerva?

42
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,559
Man, that's
a pretty weird question.

43
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:24,394
Minerva's everywhere.

44
00:02:24,436 --> 00:02:25,896
Additionally,
everyone knows that.

45
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,814
Just look around for
somebody who needs help,

46
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:30,317
and Minerva will be there
helping, obviously.

47
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,195
"Where's Minerva?"
[Chuckles]

48
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:35,572
- Thanks.
- She's everywhere?

49
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:36,657
You hear that, man?

50
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,575
Minerva's into helping people,
just like you.

51
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:41,161
She must've gave you
her helper genes as DNA

52
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:43,413
up in her womb
with your placenta.

53
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:44,790
DN-what-what?

54
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:48,085
Mister? Can I rub
your dog's tummy, mister?

55
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:50,087
He's got a cute yellow tummy.

56
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:52,339
Shoot, kid,
you don't even have to ask.

57
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:54,216
Just scooch right up
and get busy.

58
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:57,177
[Gasps]
You're a talking dog!

59
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:59,554
Teesa, Meeka, Gee-gee,
come look!

60
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,431
A talking dog!

61
00:03:01,473 --> 00:03:03,225
Are they gonna help
with the tummy rub?

62
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:05,227
-[Kids giggling]
- Finn, look.

63
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,732
Oh, geez.

64
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:12,943
I didn't think
we would find her so fast.

65
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:14,695
We can come with you
if you'd like.

66
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:18,949
Nope.
[Breathes rapidly]

67
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,325
Finn only.

68
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:22,619
Hello, young man.

69
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:24,621
Is there anything
I can help you with?

70
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,581
[Breathes deeply]

71
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,125
This is gonna sound weird,
but...

72
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:31,378
And I don't mean
to put you on the spot.

73
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:33,255
But, uh...did you...

74
00:03:34,381 --> 00:03:37,008
Did you lose...

75
00:03:37,092 --> 00:03:38,510
a son?

76
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:45,142
Careful, citizens.

77
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:47,978
Litter can be unattractive
but dangerous, as well.

78
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,523
- Uh...
- Hello, young man.

79
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,358
Is there anything
I can help you with?

80
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:57,654
This is going a lot different
than I pictured it.

81
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,491
JAKE:
Come on, now.

82
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,784
Are you telling me none of you

83
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,786
has ever seen a talking dog
before?

84
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:05,787
That's crazy.

85
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:07,497
That's even crazier
than the old lady

86
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,416
who lives alone
on that Weather Island.

87
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,752
[Laughter]

88
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,003
[Laughs]

89
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:16,381
No, but seriously,
if you think this is impressive,

90
00:04:16,465 --> 00:04:18,258
you should've seen me
at the flea circus.

91
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,886
I really stole the show.

92
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:24,264
[Laughter]

93
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:27,517
[Chuckles]
Nah, but seriously,

94
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:29,394
y'all should really
meet my friend BMO.

95
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,353
[Whispering] Jake.

96
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:31,646
JAKE:
He's a talking calculator.

97
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,898
Now's not the time.

98
00:04:33,023 --> 00:04:34,775
JAKE: Now, there's a friend
you can really...

99
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:36,485
- Whoop!
- JAKE: ...count on.

100
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,904
[Laughter]

101
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:49,039
Frieda.

102
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:54,795
JAKE:
Wow, listen, you guys are great.

103
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:56,421
I got to get going
and find my friends,

104
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:59,758
but, man, what a great crowd,
though, seriously.

105
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,384
One more joke.

106
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,261
- Yeah, come on!
- Yeah!

107
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,305
[Chuckles]
That's all I got.

108
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,765
I don't know any more jokes.

109
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:09,810
ALL:
Awww!

110
00:05:09,893 --> 00:05:10,811
Wait, wait.

111
00:05:10,894 --> 00:05:13,146
I can do other stuff
besides jokes.

112
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:15,315
Like, um, oh.

113
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,441
[Inhales deeply]

114
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:20,695
Pbbbbbbbbbht!

115
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:21,655
Huh?

116
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,406
- Mutant!
- Mutant.

117
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:24,699
- He's a mutant.
- Is he a mutant?

118
00:05:24,783 --> 00:05:26,576
What? No, no, no.

119
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:30,580
I'm just a regular dog, see?

120
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:31,957
-[Pants]
-[Gasps]

121
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,542
- He's a mutant.
- A mutant!

122
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,335
- Minerva!
- Minerva!

123
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:36,711
Minerva!

124
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:38,964
FINN: I guess this must be
pretty shocking.

125
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:41,675
Oh, are you in shock?

126
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:42,676
Do you need help?

127
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,427
MAN:
Minerva!

128
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,847
Hey.

129
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:48,598
- Minerva!
- Minerva!

130
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,725
- Minerval!
- Minerva, help!

131
00:05:52,561 --> 00:05:54,479
Oh, hey, Minerva.

132
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:57,566
Finn, I found Miner--

133
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,985
Uh, disregard.

134
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,237
You are creating a disturbance.

135
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:05,574
Please help let us help you
help us to sedate you.

136
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:07,117
I'm not a mutant.

137
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,202
I'm magic.
I think.

138
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:10,954
- Although, now that you men--
-[Poke!]

139
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,330
[Groans]

140
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,125
FINN:
Stop! He's my brother!

141
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,209
- And I'm...
-[Poke!]

142
00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:17,586
...your suhhh...

143
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:18,837
[Thud]

144
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,472
Son!

145
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:31,766
What's this?
[Grunts]

146
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,643
You can't get them off.

147
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:35,353
I tried a lot already.

148
00:06:37,606 --> 00:06:40,400
I love you, but your mom's
a hundred robe-clones.

149
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:42,110
Those things aren't my mom.

150
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:43,528
Maybe they look like my mom

151
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:45,280
because they did something
to her, right?

152
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:48,116
I'm going to get out of here
and I'm going to rescue her,

153
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:50,660
and I'll hug her, and -- and --

154
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:58,543
I've had weirder fights
than this.

155
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,424
Where the bones?

156
00:07:06,635 --> 00:07:09,429
Thas muh hand.

157
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,514
[Whirs]

158
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:12,807
[Click!]

159
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,771
[Ding!]

160
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:21,191
[Gasps]

161
00:07:21,316 --> 00:07:22,400
[Both gasp]

162
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,652
[Horns honking]

163
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,031
Uh...

164
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,077
[Pop!]

165
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,470
BMO:
It's a toy store!

166
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,597
Are you going to buy me a toy?

167
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:53,807
(\\[o

168
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,100
Well, maybe.

169
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,810
I have to talk
to my friend first.

170
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:58,603
BMO:
Mm-hmm.

171
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:05,568
I made a mistake
a long time ago.

172
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,612
My friend got hurt.

173
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:10,115
I don't know if I'm allowed
back in her life.

174
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:11,950
BMO:
Mm-hmm.

175
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:15,996
Where are we going, man?

176
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,250
[Splashing]

177
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:36,766
What is this?

178
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,061
Am I dreaming?

179
00:08:40,145 --> 00:08:41,521
Who are you?

180
00:08:41,563 --> 00:08:44,941
Uh, my name's Finn.
Are you my m--

181
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:46,317
It is you.

182
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:48,528
Oh, my gosh,
I can't believe you're alive!

183
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,322
Minerva-bot, hug my son.

184
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,283
You're beautiful.
[Laughs]

185
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,827
My My, baby Finn!

186
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,328
Oh, you're so big.

187
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,540
Last time I saw you,
you were 6.875 kilograms,

188
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,459
and now look at you!

189
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:03,460
Mom...

190
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:06,087
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
I'm babbling.

191
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:07,172
Yes, darling?

192
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,591
What happened to you?

193
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,677
You've been gone for so long.

194
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,221
When you and Martin
disappeared,

195
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:17,474
I was left
fragile as an eggshell.

196
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:22,103
Martinis a Hider.

197
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:24,105
He left with our baby.

198
00:09:24,189 --> 00:09:26,483
Dr. Gross was resolute.

199
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:30,445
She immediately activated
her most powerful Seeker

200
00:09:30,487 --> 00:09:31,946
to bring you back.

201
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:36,117
But years went by.

202
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:39,746
You and your father
were never coming back.

203
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:43,249
Dark days grew darker.

204
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:46,586
I went into myself,
and while I retreated,

205
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:49,881
Dr. Gross's work turned
strange and dangerous.

206
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,093
Aroo?

207
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,470
Dr. Gross's actions
unwittingly led

208
00:09:55,512 --> 00:09:57,388
to the release of
a terrible virus.

209
00:09:57,472 --> 00:09:59,265
[Glass shatters]

210
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:00,975
It was the most
catastrophic event

211
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:04,020
that had happened to our
species in 300 years.

212
00:10:05,647 --> 00:10:07,148
We tried to consolidate

213
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:09,484
and quarantine everyone
on Founders Island.

214
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:13,655
The fatality rate in the
general population grew to 62%.

215
00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:15,532
But the fatality rate
in Helpers,

216
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,868
those who faced the virus
daily, was 100%.

217
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:21,162
Or nearly.

218
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,791
I was only one Helper

219
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,793
and in no condition
to do my job.

220
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:28,002
[Coughs]

221
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:32,048
I made my decision.

222
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:36,636
With my brain-map
uploaded to the web,

223
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:38,805
I could be hundreds of Helpers.

224
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:42,642
And humanity needed help
above all else.

225
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:49,315
Since that day,
I have protected

226
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:52,443
and cared for all my people
the best I could.

227
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:53,820
[Sniffles]

228
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,447
But that all doesn't
matter anymore.

229
00:10:56,531 --> 00:10:57,657
You're back!

230
00:10:57,699 --> 00:11:00,535
And now you can live here
in safety.

231
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:03,079
Oh, but I can't necessarily --

232
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:05,165
For the rest of your life.

233
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:21,848
This party is so crazy!

